Test of the friction factor

The goal of this notebook is to check if the friction factor is working well. To do so, we consider a island model, and we set a friction coefficient to some iceland. If we have a friction larger than one, the number of individuals on this island shoud decrease. If its superior to one, it should increase. This can be compared to analytical results.

loading package and setting minimal simulation

devtools::load_all(pkg="../RQuantiNemo")
## Loading RQuantiNemo
parameters = list("generations" = 100,
                  "patch_capacity" = 100,
                  "patch_number" = 20,                  
                  "mating_nb_offspring_model" = 1,
                  "dispersal_model" = 0,
                  "dispersal_rate" = 0.1,
                  "replicates" = 25,
                  "stat" = "{adlt.nbInd_p}")
my_sim.base = new("simulation",sim.dir = "friction/", parameters = parameters)

Result

No dispersal factor

Launching simulation

my_sim = my_sim.base
my_sim@sim.name <- "no_friction"
success <- run(my_sim, verbose = FALSE)
## printing into :friction/no_friction.ini
## excuting /Users/frederic/Desktop/RQuantiNemo/quantiNemo2 friction/no_friction.ini

Ploting result

stat <- loadStat(my_sim)
plot(stat$adlt.nbInd_p01, main = "Evolution of the number of individual", ylab = "Nb of individual", xlab = "generations", ylim = c(90,110), type = "l")
for (patch in 1:20) {
  var = paste("adlt.nbInd_p",formatC(patch, width = 2,  flag = "0"),sep="")
  lines(stat[[var]])  
}

All dispersal factor set to 1

Launching simulation

my_sim = my_sim.base
my_sim@sim.name <- "1_friction"
my_sim <- setParameter(my_sim, "patch_friction", "{rep(1,12)}")
success <- run(my_sim, verbose = FALSE)
## printing into :friction/1_friction.ini
## excuting /Users/frederic/Desktop/RQuantiNemo/quantiNemo2 friction/1_friction.ini

Ploting result

stat <- loadStat(my_sim)
plot(stat$adlt.nbInd_p01, main = "Evolution of the number of individual", ylab = "Nb of individual", xlab = "generations", ylim = c(90,110), type = "l")
for (patch in 1:20) {
  var = paste("adlt.nbInd_p",formatC(patch, width = 2,  flag = "0"),sep="")
